         <div xml:lang="en" type="translation">
            <ab>The 12th year of Lucius Septimius Severus Pius Pertinax and  Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Pius, [[and Publius Septimius Geta Caesar Augustus]], Pauni 15. We, Chairemon, son of Asklas, and his associates in the allotment of the sitologia of the village of Kerkesoucha, have received at the granary of the aforesaid village from the produce of the same year by leveled public measure . . . for catoecic land of Kerkesoucha exploited through the possessors of catoecic land of Karanis, from Horion son of Apolinarius, four artabai of wheat.</ab>
